## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of nation in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Nation is the bounded jurisdictional and policy-bearing unit
that organizes territory,
population affiliation,
institutional authority,
law/policy effect,
and sovereign or semi-sovereign governance logic.

Nation is not merely a label for geography.
It is the structure that gives
policy effect,
jurisdictional belonging,
and collective authority
their bounded meaning.

## architectural_position
Nation sits between:
- world containment
- territory/map relation
- governance and vote structures
- law/admin/security effect
- family/work/company/policy consequences
- cross-nation relation and trade consequences

## required_behavior
- nation identity must remain explicit
- nation boundary must remain explicit
- jurisdiction and belonging must remain explicit
- current and historical nation states must remain distinguishable
- policy-bearing authority must remain explicit

## canonical_rules
- nation truth must not be replaced by projection
- territorial association must not imply unrestricted authority
- historical nation state must remain queryable
- cross-nation meaning must remain explicit
- ambiguous jurisdiction fails closed

## state_model
The nation domain distinguishes:
- proposed nation state
- active nation state
- restricted nation state
- transformed nation state
- historical nation state
- dissolved nation state

## actor_boundary
- national authority
- national operator
- national reviewer
- external adapter

## decision_matrix
- if nation identity is unresolved, stop jurisdictional action
- if territorial/jurisdictional scope is unclear, fail closed
- if cross-nation effect is requested, require explicit boundary handling
- if nation is historical or dissolved, preserve historical distinction

## review_checklist
- nation identity is explicit
- jurisdiction boundary is explicit
- state model is explicit
- cross-nation distinction is explicit
